What you need to know:  The event will bring together athletes from five counties namely Turkana, Elgeyo Marakwet, Trans Nzoia, West Pokot and Samburu counties who will be battling it out for slots at the National Cross Country ChampionshipsFormer World Under-20 3,000m silver medalist Zenah Jemutai, who has been training at the Kapsait Athletics Camp in Elgeyo Marakwet County is optimistic that her participation at cross country events will help her have a good season in track this yearRepresenting West Pokot County, Charles Lokir who trains at Iten is also confident of a good race despite missing a slot at the national trials where he finished ninth